        "content": "<p>Why? Now I have to type an extra <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">⊤</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\top</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊤</span></span></span></span> and it is less perspicuous :-(</p>",
        "id": 486273383,
        "sender_full_name": "Dominic Steinitz",
        "timestamp": 1733395087
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See this thread: <a href=\"#narrow/channel/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.60HolomorphicOn.60.20and.20.60HolomorphicAt.60\">#PR reviews&gt;&#96;HolomorphicOn&#96; and &#96;HolomorphicAt&#96;</a> </p>\n<p>In short: the current setup required reformulating all lemmas about <code>ContMDiff</code> also in terms of <code>Smooth</code>.<br>\nYou can of course (locally) still add notation that <code>Smooth</code> means  <code>ContMDiff</code> with <code>n = \\top</code>, but you should for lemmas in Mathlib that are about ContMDiff.</p>",
